ha, I had to rebuild msdb this weekend myself  :-)&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
mdb was suspect, sql agent wouldn&#039;t start etc etc&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In that case you need to start sql server with traceflag 3608&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
start sqlservr.exe -c -T3608&lt;br /&gt;
then detach the DB and delete the data and log files 9or rename them), then you run instmsdb.sql from the install directory, restart sql server normal. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Now you have to grab a backup of msdb and restore it so that you have all your jobs back. Or if you have source control you can run the scripts for all the jobs
